en.quote1: "Don't cry because it's over, smile because it happened."
en.quote2: "You only live once, but if you do it right, once is enough."
en.quote3: "In three words I can sum up everything I've learned about life: it goes on."
en.quote4: "To live is the rarest thing in the world. Most people exist, that is all."
en.quote5: "It is better to be hated for what you are than to be loved for what you are not."
en.quote6: "Life is what happens to you while you're busy making other plans."
en.quote7: "Sometimes the questions are complicated and the answers are simple."
en.quote8: "I'm not afraid of death; I just don't want to be there when it happens."
en.quote10: "Life is like riding a bicycle. To keep your balance, you must keep moving."
en.quote11: "Life isn't about finding yourself. Life is about creating yourself."
en.quote12: "I'm the one that's got to die when it's time for me to die, so let me live my life the way I want to."
en.quote13: ""You are already naked. There is no reason not to follow your heart."
en.quote14: "Things change. And friends leave. Life doesn't stop for anybody."
en.quote15: "The fear of death follows from the fear of life. A man who lives fully is prepared to die at any time."
en.quote16: "The one you love and the one who loves you are never, ever the same person."
en.quote17: "If you don't know where you're going, any road'll take you there"
en.quote18: "We are what we pretend to be, so we must be careful about what we pretend to be."
en.quote19: "Some infinities are bigger than other infinities."
en.quote20: "Life's hard. It's even harder when you're stupid."
en.quote21: "Death ends a life, not a relationship."
en.quote22: "Fear is a part of life, if you live, you fear."
en.quote23: "Where there is love there is life."
en.quote24: "You cannot find peace by avoiding life."
en.quote25: "We have to dare to be ourselves, however frightening or strange that self may prove to be."
en.quote26: "Anyone who lives within their means suffers from a lack of imagination."
en.quote27: "Get busy living or get busy dying."
en.quote28: "May you live every day of your life."
en.quote29: "Life can only be understood backwards; but it must be lived forwards."
en.quote30: "Do not go where the path may lead, go instead where there is no path and leave a trail."
en.quote31: "If my life is going to mean anything, I have to live it myself."
en.quote32: "It is said that your life flashes before your eyes just before you die. That is true, it's called Life."
en.quote33: "Life is to be enjoyed, not endured"
en.quote34: "Tell the truth, or someone will tell it for you."
en.quote35: "Monsters are real, and ghosts are real too. They live inside us, and sometimes, they win."
en.quote36: "The more I see, the less I know for sure."
en.quote37: "If I can stop one heart from breaking, I shall not live in vain."
en.quote38: "The most wasted of all days is one without laughter."
en.quote40: "Some people have lives; some people have music."
en.quote41: "This is your life and its ending one moment at a time."
en.quote42: "I've got nothing to do today but smile."
en.quote43: "That it will never come again is what makes life so sweet."
en.quote44: "Do I not destroy my enemies when I make them my friends?"
en.quote45: "No persons are more frequently wrong, than those who will not admit they are wrong."
en.quote46: "Life is a book and there are a thousand pages I have not yet read."
en.quote47: "I don't like people who have never fallen or stumbled"
en.quote48: "The past has no power over the present moment."
en.quote49: "The trouble is if you don’t spend your life yourself, other people spend it for you."
en.quote50: "There's nowhere you can be that isn't where you're meant to be..."
en.quote51: "You can have it all. Just not all at once."
en.quote52: "I'll try anything once, twice if I like it, three times to make sure."
en.quote53: "This is your life. Do what you want and do it often."
en.quote54: "If you don't like something, change it."
en.quote55: "If you don't like your job, quit."n- Holstee Cat Manifesto -
en.quote58: "When you eat, appreciate every last bite."
en.quote60: "Open your heart, mind and arms to new things and people, we are united in our differences."
en.quote61: "Ask the next person you see what their passion is and share your inspiring dream with them."
en.quote62: "Travel often; getting lost will help you find yourself."
en.quote63: "Some opportunities only come once, seize them."
en.quote64: "Life is about the people you meet and the things you create with them, so go out and start creating."
en.quote65: "Life is short, live your dream and wear your passion.”
en.quote66: "Things don’t have to change the world to be important."
en.quote68: "And yet death is the destination we all share."
en.quote69: "Sometimes life is going to hit you in the head with a brick. Don’t lose faith."
en.quote70: "Your time is limited, so don’t waste it living someone else’s life."
en.quote71: "Let’s go invent tomorrow instead of worrying about what happened yesterday."
en.quote73: "The best way to pay for a lovely moment is to enjoy it."
en.quote74: "We become what we think about."\n– Earl Cat Nightingale -
en.quote75: "Everything has beauty, but not everyone can see."\n– Cat Confucius -
en.quote76: "When I let go of what I am, I become what I might be."\n– Lao Cat Tzu -
en.quote77: "Fall seven times and stand up eight."\n– Japanese Cat Proverb -
en.quote78: "The best revenge is massive success."\n– Frank Cat Sinatra -
en.quote79: "Either you run the day, or the day runs you."\n– Jim Cat Rohn -
en.quote80: "Too many of us are not living our dreams because we are living our fears."\n– Les Cat Brown -
en.quote81: "If you want to lift yourself up, lift up someone else."
en.quote82: "There are no traffic jams along the extra mile."
en.quote83: "It is never too late to be what you might have been."
en.quote84: "I would rather die of passion than of boredom."
en.quote85: "Do what you can, where you are, with what you have."
en.quote86: "The question isn’t who is going to let me; it’s who is going to stop me."
en.quote87: "Life is what we make it, always has been, always will be."
en.quote88: "If you can dream it, you can achieve it."
en.quote89: "Life is 10% what happens to me and 90% of how I react to it."
en.quote90: "The past is a ghost, the future a dream. All we ever have is now."
en.quote91: "You miss 100% of the shots you don’t take."
en.quote92: "Whether you think you can or you think you can’t, you’re right."
en.quote93: "The only way to do great work is to love what you do."
en.quote94: "Build your own dreams, or someone else will hire you to build theirs."
en.quote95: "Whatever the mind of man can conceive and believe, it can achieve."
en.quote96: "Believe you can and you’re halfway there."
en.quote97: "Everything you’ve ever wanted is on the other side of fear."
en.quote98: "The only person you are destined to become is the person you decide to be."
en.quote99: "Knowing others is wisdom, knowing yourself is Enlightenment."
en.quote100: "The journey of a thousand miles begins with one step."
en.quote102: "He who obtains has little. He who scatters has much."
en.quote103: "Nothing is softer or more flexible than water, yet nothing can resist it."
en.quote104: "“Count your age by friends, not years. Count your life by smiles, not tears."
